workoutPlan:
**100-Minute Beginner Chest & Biceps Workout**

**I. Warm-up (10 minutes)**

* Light Cardio: (5 minutes)  e.g., Jumping Jacks, High Knees, Arm Circles
* Dynamic Stretching: (5 minutes) Arm swings, torso twists, shoulder rotations


**II. Chest (40 minutes)**

* Incline Push-Ups: 3 sets of 8-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Resistance Band Chest Press: 3 sets of 12-15 reps (8 minutes)
* Pec Deck Machine: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Chest Press Machine: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Bodyweight Flyes: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)


**III. Biceps (40 minutes)**

* Resistance Band Curls: 3 sets of 15-20 reps (8 minutes)
* Wide-grip barbell curl: 3 sets of 8-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Biceps curl to shoulder press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Incline Hammer Curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)
* Flexor Incline Dumbbell Curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (8 minutes)


**IV. Cool-down (10 minutes)**

* Static Stretching: (10 minutes) Hold each stretch for 30 seconds.  Focus on chest and biceps stretches.  (e.g., Chest stretch, Bicep stretch, Tricep stretch)


**Note:** Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets. Adjust the number of sets and reps based on your fitness level.  If you find an exercise too difficult, reduce the reps or sets, or use lighter weight/resistance.  Prioritize proper form over the number of repetitions.  Consult a physician before starting any new workout routine.
